  <ns6859:para xmlns:ns6859="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns6860:emphasis xmlns:ns6860="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vi</ns6860:emphasis> and its enhanced version, <ns6861:emphasis xmlns:ns6861="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vim</ns6861:emphasis>,
    which stands for <ns6862:emphasis xmlns:ns6862="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vi-improved</ns6862:emphasis>, are perhaps the most widely
    used editors on Unix-based systems, and it is essential that any Linux user has at
    least a rudimentary working knowledge of <ns6863:emphasis xmlns:ns6863="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vi</ns6863:emphasis>.
  </ns6859:para>

